# Claude Design System (UI/UX)

Source of truth: [DESIGN.md](mdc:DESIGN.md)

When building or changing UI, match Claude.com marketing/product surfaces:

- Canvas: warm cream `{colors.canvas}` `#faf9f5` — never cool gray or pure white
- Primary accent: coral `{colors.primary}` `#cc785c` — scarce on buttons, generous only on full-bleed callouts
- Surfaces trinity only: cream canvas → cream cards (`#efe9de`) → dark navy (`#181715`); alternate bands, never repeat the same mode twice in a row
- Display: slab-serif (Copernicus / Cormorant Garamond / EB Garamond) weight 400 + negative tracking — never bold, never Inter for headlines
- Body/UI: Inter / humanist sans 400–500
- Depth: color-block first, hairline borders; shadows rare
- Radius: 8px buttons/inputs, 12px cards, 16px hero, pills for badges
- Section rhythm: 96px; card padding: 32px
- Use token refs from DESIGN.md; do not invent purple/cyan/green brand accents

Do not follow generic “AI SaaS” cool-white/blue aesthetics. Prefer cream + coral + dark navy editorial pacing.
